<p>The goal is to keep things short, and keep things moving. You get five minutes to read, maximum. <em>There is no minimum time limit</em>. Â And yes, youâ€™re allowed to read more than one thing, so long as the total length of everything you read isnâ€™t longer than five minutes. Beforehand, <strong>practice</strong> reading your thing aloud. Time yourself. If your thing is funny, factor in audience laughter. If your thing is longer than five minutes, pick something shorter, or cut something out. Onstage, itâ€™s often hard to knowÂ how long youâ€™ve been reading. At most live events, weâ€™ll have a laptop or iPad with a timerÂ on it, so you can check and see how youâ€™re doing time-wise.</p>

